We don't want to impose this on all developers and so we leave this traversal to the notification recipients which need it.

- `FEE_ADDED_AT_CHECKOUT`: The fee is shown in addition to the ticket price at checkout and a guest pays the fee. For example, if you sell tickets for $10, a customer will see a service fee of $0.25 and will pay $10.25 in total.

members.doc: Whether this ticket definition is hidden to site visitors and can't be purchased.

members.name: initialLimit
members.doc: The maximum number of tickets that can be sold for the event when first defining the event. If a seating map is defined after you created a ticket definition, this property is ignored and `actualLimit` is used instead.

members.name: limitPerCheckout
members.doc:
Number of tickets that can be purchased per checkout.
**Note:** If the `actuaLimit` or `salesDetails.unsoldCount` field value is smaller than `limitPerCheckout`, then it overrides this field.

members.name: limited
members.doc: Whether the ticket has a limited maximum quantity.

members.name: revision
members.doc: Revision number, which increments by 1 each time the ticket definition is updated. To prevent conflicting changes, the existing revision must be used when updating a ticket definition.

members.name: saleStatus
members.doc:
Ticket sale status. Possible values:
- `SALE_SCHEDULED`: Tickets are not on sale yet.
- `SALE_STARTED`: Tickets are on sale.
- `SALE_ENDED`: Tickets are not on sale.

members.name: salesDetails
members.doc:
Ticket sales information.
**Note:** This field is only returned when `SALES_DETAILS` fieldset is included in the request.

members.name: _updatedDate
members.doc: Date and time of the ticket definition summary latest update in `yyyy-mm-ddThh:mm:sssZ` format.

members.name: eventId
members.doc: Event ID to which the ticket definition summary belongs.

members.name: highestTicketPriceFormatted
members.doc: Formatted price of highest priced ticket.

members.name: lowestTicketPriceFormatted
members.doc: Formatted price of lowest priced ticket.

members.name: soldOut
members.doc: Whether all tickets are sold for this event.

members.name: guestAssignedTickets
members.doc: Whether the form must be filled out separately for each ticket.

members.name: reservationDurationInMinutes
members.doc: Duration for which the tickets being bought are reserved.

members.name: ticketLimitPerOrder
members.doc: Limit of tickets that can be purchased per order, default 20.

members.name: currencyLocked
members.doc: Whether currency is locked and cannot be changed (generally occurs after the first order in the specified currency has been created).

members.name: revenue
members.doc:
Total revenue, excluding fees.
(taxes and payment provider fees are not deducted.)

members.name: message
members.doc: Message shown when event tickets are unavailable.

members.name: fields
members.doc:
Predefined sets of fields to return.
- `SALES_DETAILS`: Returns `salesDetails`.

members.name: revision
members.doc: The revision of the ticket definition

members.name: sortIndex
members.doc: the sort index of a ticket definition to set

members.name: metaSiteId
members.doc: the msid the URI is on

members.name: uriPath
members.doc: URI path to invalidate (e.g. page/my/path) - without leading/trailing slashes
